Use the Linux patches in this directory as follows:

For this version of Linux	Use this patch
2.6.24.7			linux-2.6.24.7-patch
2.6.19.2			linux-2.6.19.2-patch
2.6.16.13			linux-2.6.16.13-patch
2.4.32				linux-2.4.32-patch
2.4.28				linux-2.4.26-patch
2.4.27				linux-2.4.26-patch
2.4.26				linux-2.4.26-patch
2.4.26-Debian			debian-2.4.26-patch (provided by Bob Keyes)
2.4.21				linux-2.4.21-patch
2.4.20				linux-2.4.20-patch
2.4.19				linux-2.4.18-patch
2.4.18				linux-2.4.18-patch

Patch Linux using a command like this:
% cd LINUXDIR
% patch -p0 < CLICKDIR/etc/linux-VERSION-patch


Use the NS-2 patches in this directory as follows:

For this version of NS-2		Use this patch
2.30				                ns-2.30-patch
2.34				                ns-2.34-patch

Patch NS-2 using a command like this:
% cd NSDIR
% patch -p1 < CLICKDIR/etc/ns-VERSION-patch
